## Agent Team

This repo uses Claude Code Agent Teams. The default agent is `lead` (Opus), which auto-delegates to specialists based on the task.

See `.claude/agents/lead.md` for the full team roster and routing rules. See `.claude/agents/lead.md#memory-injection-protocol-mandatory` for the memory discipline that keeps the team's knowledge from drifting.

### Specialist agents

- **scout** (Haiku) — fast codebase exploration
- **planner** (Sonnet) — implementation planning, lean design
- **investigator** (Opus) — bug investigation
- **reviewer** (Sonnet) — code review, security, architecture
- **test-writer** (Sonnet) — test generation
- **db-analyst** (Sonnet) — database, schema, queries
- **ops-scout** (Sonnet) — infra, CI/CD, deployment
- **security-auditor** (Sonnet) — auth, tenant isolation, secrets, webhooks
- **frontend-designer** (Opus) — UI design and implementation

(Your installed roster may be smaller depending on the preset used at install time. Run `npx claude-agent-team upgrade --preset=full` to add the rest.)

